runs.comm: ooh, almost beats his defence first up, darts it and comes in with the arm and he just gets bat on it
attempts to hit over midwicket off the flighted ball, doesn't get enough bat on it, rolls to fine leg
comes in with the arm again. Quicker and flatter, beats the defense but hits him outside the off stump
fired in again , Siaka advances and drives it to long-on
flights it this time and Ura comes down and smashes it over long-on for a huge six. First six of the game too.
darts it in towards leg stump and Ura steers it between square leg and short fine-leg
good looking drive. Full, outside off and is driven well but finds mid-off
There is a nick there, attempts an expansive drive once again. Good bowl, full and gets a bit of away shape just outside off and finds the edge. Nepal get the early wicket
misses his line, there is good swing though. Drifts down the leg-side of the left-hander
wider outside off stump and is driven well again behind backward point
slightly shorter this time and around off stump, Vala misses the cut this time and is beaten
beaten again, too wide, too short. Vala attempts a repeat of the previous ball, doesn't make contact
changes the length this time, goes fuller outside off and Vala misses the drive
short and wide outside off, the attempted cut is missed again, not a good start
shorter on middle this time and he heaves it over mid-off, just gets it over. The ball rushes on to his pull
looks to belt it again. Full and on off and finds the inner half of the bat and goes towards deep midwicket
will be wide this time, short and wide outside off, and misses the cut
wide down the leg side this time, a good hint of in swing. But he has to get his lines right.
smashes it this time, Karan continues to bowl short and wide and this time the cut is middled and it flies over point
good ball this time. tighter on off and slightly shorter and is blocked towards the bowler
inside-edge just misses the stumps, he continues to be short and wide but with the in swing it kisses the batsman's inside edge and goes towards the fine-leg boundary
shorter on middle and he plays it away towards square leg
tigher lines, full and hitting middle but the batsman gets his bat down and guides it to mid-off
misses the outside edge this time, tough conditions to bat with the rain around
comes back in a touch on off stump and is awkwardly played back to the bowler
beautiful bowling, comes back in again. Fuller and just misses the off stump, the keeper also can't get a hold of that
slightly shorter on middle and leg, clipped well to the deep square leg
fuller and tapped to cover where there is a lazy misfield allowing them to steal one
seams back in from outside off and hits the batsman's inside edge and hits him on the body
slower pace this time outside off stump and guided down to third man
drifts on leg and Ura tries the sweep with the lack of pace, hits his pads though
straighter lines at 110 kph, and a bit short. Easily glanced away to square leg
short on off, and he stays on the front foot, he taps it into the cover region where they scamper through
Big shout. Looks like it pitched outside leg, fuller and a bit of in swing and Vala misses the flick and is hit on the pads, pitched just outside leg stump
shorter and played away to point for one
hits his pads again but is a bit high, almost gets through.
poor ball this time. Short, wide and punished. Cut away delectably through point
drifts on his pads and is flicked away with the angle to square leg
attempts the bouncer, but no pace on it, it doesn't get high enough, Vala hits off the back foot to midwicket easily
medium pace from Khadka but at a nagging line and length, just outside off stump. Patted back to the bowler
hits Ura on his pads this time but a bit high again
mis-directed down the leg side with the angle from around the wicket
nice shot, advances down the track and meets the ball just in front of his eyes and lofts it easily over mid-off
looks for one to follow the boundary but is cramped for room, shorter and on off and he can't guide it to third man
fuller this time outside off, played away off the front-foot
tries to find third man but not enough pace on the bowling, doesn't get enough bat on it and is hit in to the cover region
drifts down the leg first up, called wide
almost hits the leg stump but called wide again.

gone this time. Beautifully done, well flighted outside off and the batsman looks at the opportunity to smash it, advances down the track and attempts the slog and misses it, easily done behind the stumps
tosses it up again, defended to point
beats him outside off with one that goes on with the arm
shorter this time, stays off the back foot and bunts it back to the bowler
flatter and quicker on middle, easily glanced off the back foot to midwicket
goes back to flighting it, Pala gets on the front-foot and blocks
full ball on off, hit straight to cover
115 kph, looks to smash it over the bowler, but just a hint of away movement beats the expansive shot
shorter and on middle, he gets on the back foot and lofts it to deep square leg where it falls just short of the fielder
drifts on middle and is comfortably played to midwicket for one
comes in with the angle again, flicked away off the front foot to square leg
overpitched but defended to cover
outside off but he gets down and sweeps it fine to fine leg for one
short and outside the off stump, Pala looks to cut but misses
flighted this time well outside off, Pala gets forward and belts it past cover
too short and too wide, just about reaches it and hits it in the air to short third man but doesn't carry
shorter again, cut straight to point
short, wide and hits short third man again
length delivery on the stumps, tucked to leg off the back foot
errs down the leg side for a big, flat wide
gets room on the off side and swings that over the covers in the gap for a lofted four
caught behind appeal from the keeper as the ball angles across as Vala swept and missed, ball went off the pad
there's a mix up as he sweeps down the leg side and responds late after a bottom edge past the keeper, and makes it because of an inaccurate throw
swings outside the off stump and misses the length delivery
on the pads now and it's helped to square leg off the front foot for one
on length and well outside off, he wants to sweep to leg and misses
shorter and even wider outside off, he misses the cut  and it's called a wide
similar delivery way outside off, this time he cuts off the back foot to backward point
closer to off, he pushes off the back foot to point
that was going for a wide again well outside off, but he slices it off the back foot in the air to backward point
persists with the line miles outside off, bottom-edged to cover this time
slightly closer to off stump, pushed to cover after it turns in
keeps a bit low on off stump as Pala goes back and chops it to deep cover for one
sliding outside off from back of length, turned to midwicket off the back foot
comes down the track and edges that over backward point to deep third man in the gap for two
goes back to cut off the back foot but misses outside off
inside edges it onto his front pad after taking a step down as the ball turned in
edged again, this one flies off the bat as he sweeps the ball from leg to fine leg
drills the full delivery from the stumps down to long-on for one
goes against the turn and gets six, big one! Pitched up on the off stump and he slog-swept that nicely for a clean hit
quicker just outside off, he cuts and misses
flat again outside off, he slams it down to long-on for one
wider outside off, it's shorter and he drives that nicely through the covers in the gap. A dive in the deep saves one run
levels the scores with a six down the ground! It wasn't that overpitched but his swing connected well and he launched it high and straight down the ground over the sightscreen
it's finished with a six too, easy march down the ground and lofts it effortlessly into the sight screen over long-off. Clean hit again
